36* code for Text compaction

38static const int TEXT_COMPACTION = 0;

41* code for Byte compaction

45/**
46* code for Numeric compaction
47*/
48static const int NUMERIC_COMPACTION = 2;

50/**
51* Text compaction submode Alpha
52*/
53static const int SUBMODE_ALPHA = 0;
54
55/**
56* Text compaction submode Lower
57*/
58static const int SUBMODE_LOWER = 1;
59
60/**
61* Text compaction submode Mixed

63static const int SUBMODE_MIXED = 2;

66* Text compaction submode Punctuation

68static const int SUBMODE_PUNCTUATION = 3;

70/**
71* mode latch to Text Compaction mode
72*/
73static const int LATCH_TO_TEXT = 900;
74
75/**
76* mode latch to Byte Compaction mode (number of characters NOT a multiple of 6)
77*/
78static const int LATCH_TO_BYTE_PADDED = 901;

80/**
81* mode latch to Numeric Compaction mode
82*/
83static const int LATCH_TO_NUMERIC = 902;
84
85/**
86* mode shift to Byte Compaction mode
87*/
88static const int SHIFT_TO_BYTE = 913;
89
90/**
91* mode latch to Byte Compaction mode (number of characters a multiple of 6)
92*/
93static const int LATCH_TO_BYTE = 924;

164static void EncodingECI(int eci, std::vector<int>& buffer)
165{
166 if (eci >= 0 && eci < 900) {
167 buffer.push_back(ECI_CHARSET);
168 buffer.push_back(eci);
169 }
170 else if (eci < 810900) {
171 buffer.push_back(ECI_GENERAL_PURPOSE);
172 buffer.push_back(eci / 900 - 1);
173 buffer.push_back(eci % 900);
174 }
175 else if (eci < 811800) {
176 buffer.push_back(ECI_USER_DEFINED);
177 buffer.push_back(810900 - eci);
178 }
179 else {
180 throw std::invalid_argument("ECI number not in valid range from 0..811799");
181 }
182}
183
184static inline bool IsDigit(int ch)
185{
186 return ch >= '0' && ch <= '9';
187}
188
189static inline bool IsAlphaUpper(int ch)
190{
191 return ch == ' ' || (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z');
192}
193
194static inline bool IsAlphaLower(int ch)
195{
196 return ch == ' ' || (ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z');
197}
198
199static bool IsMixed(int ch)
200{
201 return (ch & 0x7f) == ch && MIXED[ch] != -1;
202}
203
204static bool IsPunctuation(int ch)
205{
206 return (ch & 0x7f) == ch && PUNCTUATION[ch] != -1;
207}
208
209static bool IsText(int ch)
210{
211 return ch == '\t' || ch == '\n' || ch == '\r' || (ch >= 32 && ch <= 126);
212}

215/**
216* Encode parts of the message using Text Compaction as described in ISO/IEC 15438:2001(E),
217* chapter 4.4.2.
218*
219* @param msg the message
220* @param startpos the start position within the message
221* @param count the number of characters to encode
222* @param sb receives the encoded codewords
223* @param initialSubmode should normally be SUBMODE_ALPHA
224* @return the text submode in which this method ends
225*/
226static int EncodeText(const std::wstring& msg, int startpos, int count, int submode, std::vector<int>& output)
227{
228 std::vector<int> tmp;
229 tmp.reserve(count);
230 int idx = 0;
231 while (true) {
232 int ch = msg[startpos + idx];
233 switch (submode) {
234 case SUBMODE_ALPHA:
235 if (IsAlphaUpper(ch)) {
236 tmp.push_back(ch == ' ' ? 26 : (ch - 65)); //space
237 }
238 else if (IsAlphaLower(ch)) {
239 submode = SUBMODE_LOWER;
240 tmp.push_back(27); //ll
241 continue;
242 }
243 else if (IsMixed(ch)) {
244 submode = SUBMODE_MIXED;
245 tmp.push_back(28); //ml
246 continue;
247 }
248 else {
249 tmp.push_back(29); //ps
250 tmp.push_back(PUNCTUATION[ch]);
251 }
252 break;
253 case SUBMODE_LOWER:
254 if (IsAlphaLower(ch)) {
255 tmp.push_back(ch == ' ' ? 26 : (ch - 97)); //space
256 }
257 else if (IsAlphaUpper(ch)) {
258 tmp.push_back(27); //as
259 tmp.push_back(ch - 65);
260 //space cannot happen here, it is also in "Lower"
261 }
262 else if (IsMixed(ch)) {
263 submode = SUBMODE_MIXED;
264 tmp.push_back(28); //ml
265 continue;
266 }
267 else {
268 tmp.push_back(29); //ps
269 tmp.push_back(PUNCTUATION[ch]);
270 }
271 break;
272 case SUBMODE_MIXED:
273 if (IsMixed(ch)) {
274 tmp.push_back(MIXED[ch]);
275 }
276 else if (IsAlphaUpper(ch)) {
277 submode = SUBMODE_ALPHA;
278 tmp.push_back(28); //al
279 continue;
280 }
281 else if (IsAlphaLower(ch)) {
282 submode = SUBMODE_LOWER;
283 tmp.push_back(27); //ll
284 continue;
285 }
286 else {
287 if (startpos + idx + 1 < count) {
288 int next = msg[startpos + idx + 1];
289 if (IsPunctuation(next)) {
290 submode = SUBMODE_PUNCTUATION;
291 tmp.push_back(25); //pl
292 continue;
293 }
294 }
295 tmp.push_back(29); //ps
296 tmp.push_back(PUNCTUATION[ch]);
297 }
298 break;
299 default: //SUBMODE_PUNCTUATION
300 if (IsPunctuation(ch)) {
301 tmp.push_back(PUNCTUATION[ch]);
302 }
303 else {
304 submode = SUBMODE_ALPHA;
305 tmp.push_back(29); //al
306 continue;
307 }
308 }
309 idx++;
310 if (idx >= count) {
311 break;
312 }
313 }
314 int h = 0;
315 size_t len = tmp.size();
316 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {
317 bool odd = (i % 2) != 0;
318 if (odd) {
319 h = (h * 30) + tmp[i];
320 output.push_back(h);
321 }
322 else {
323 h = tmp[i];
324 }
325 }
326 if ((len % 2) != 0) {
327 output.push_back((h * 30) + 29); //ps
328 }
329 return submode;
330}

333/**
334* Encode parts of the message using Byte Compaction as described in ISO/IEC 15438:2001(E),
335* chapter 4.4.3. The Unicode characters will be converted to binary using the cp437
336* codepage.
337*
338* @param bytes the message converted to a byte array
339* @param startpos the start position within the message
340* @param count the number of bytes to encode
341* @param startmode the mode from which this method starts
342* @param sb receives the encoded codewords
343*/
344static void EncodeBinary(const std::string& bytes, int startpos, int count, int startmode, std::vector<int>& output)
345{
346 if (count == 1 && startmode == TEXT_COMPACTION) {
347 output.push_back(SHIFT_TO_BYTE);
348 }
349 else {
350 if ((count % 6) == 0) {
351 output.push_back(LATCH_TO_BYTE);
352 }
353 else {
354 output.push_back(LATCH_TO_BYTE_PADDED);
355 }
356 }
357
358 int idx = startpos;
359 // Encode sixpacks
360 if (count >= 6) {
361 int chars[5];
362 while ((startpos + count - idx) >= 6) {
363 long t = 0;
364 for (int i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
365 t <<= 8;
366 t += bytes[idx + i] & 0xff;
367 }
368 for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
369 chars[i] = t % 900;
370 t /= 900;
371 }
372 for (int i = 4; i >= 0; i--) {
373 output.push_back(chars[i]);
374 }
375 idx += 6;
376 }
377 }
378 //Encode rest (remaining n<5 bytes if any)
379 for (int i = idx; i < startpos + count; i++) {
380 int ch = bytes[i] & 0xff;
381 output.push_back(ch);
382 }
383}

386static void EncodeNumeric(const std::wstring& msg, int startpos, int count, std::vector<int>& output)
387{
388 int idx = 0;
389 std::vector<int> tmp;
390 tmp.reserve(count / 3 + 1);
391 BigInteger num900(900);
392 while (idx < count) {
393 tmp.clear();
394 int len = std::min(44, count - idx);
395 auto part = L"1" + msg.substr(startpos + idx, len);
396
397 BigInteger bigint, r;
398 BigInteger::TryParse(part, bigint);
399 do {
400 BigInteger::Divide(bigint, num900, bigint, r);
401 tmp.push_back(r.toInt());
402 } while (!bigint.isZero());
403
404 //Reverse temporary string
405 output.insert(output.end(), tmp.rbegin(), tmp.rend());
406 idx += len;
407 }
408}

411/**
412* Determines the number of consecutive characters that are encodable using numeric compaction.
413*
414* @param msg the message
415* @param startpos the start position within the message
416* @return the requested character count
417*/
418static int DetermineConsecutiveDigitCount(const std::wstring& msg, int startpos)
419{
420 int count = 0;
421 size_t len = msg.length();
422 size_t idx = startpos;
423 if (idx < len) {
424 int ch = msg[idx];
425 while (IsDigit(ch) && idx < len) {
426 count++;
427 idx++;
428 if (idx < len) {
429 ch = msg[idx];
430 }
431 }
432 }
433 return count;
434}
435
436/**
437* Determines the number of consecutive characters that are encodable using text compaction.
438*
439* @param msg the message
440* @param startpos the start position within the message
441* @return the requested character count
442*/
443static int DetermineConsecutiveTextCount(const std::wstring& msg, int startpos)
444{
445 size_t len = msg.length();
446 size_t idx = startpos;
447 while (idx < len) {
448 int ch = msg[idx];
449 int numericCount = 0;
450 while (numericCount < 13 && IsDigit(ch) && idx < len) {
451 numericCount++;
452 idx++;
453 if (idx < len) {
454 ch = msg[idx];
455 }
456 }
457 if (numericCount >= 13) {
458 return static_cast<int>(idx - startpos - numericCount);
459 }
460 if (numericCount > 0) {
461 //Heuristic: All text-encodable chars or digits are binary encodable
462 continue;
463 }
464 ch = msg[idx];
465
466 //Check if character is encodable
467 if (!IsText(ch)) {
468 break;
469 }
470 idx++;
471 }
472 return static_cast<int>(idx - startpos);
473}
474
475/**
476* Determines the number of consecutive characters that are encodable using binary compaction.
477*
478* @param msg the message
479* @param startpos the start position within the message
480* @param encoding the charset used to convert the message to a byte array
481* @return the requested character count
482*/
483static int DetermineConsecutiveBinaryCount(const std::wstring& msg, int startpos)
484{
485 size_t len = msg.length();
486 size_t idx = startpos;
487 while (idx < len) {
488 int ch = msg[idx];
489 int numericCount = 0;
490
491 while (numericCount < 13 && IsDigit(ch)) {
492 numericCount++;
493 //textCount++;
494 size_t i = idx + numericCount;
495 if (i >= len) {
496 break;
497 }
498 ch = msg[i];
499 }
500 if (numericCount >= 13) {
501 return static_cast<int>(idx - startpos);
502 }
503 idx++;
504 }
505 return static_cast<int>(idx - startpos);
506}

508/**
509* Performs high-level encoding of a PDF417 message using the algorithm described in annex P
510* of ISO/IEC 15438:2001(E). If byte compaction has been selected, then only byte compaction
511* is used.
512*
513* @param msg the message
514* @param compaction compaction mode to use
515* @param encoding character encoding used to encode in default or byte compaction
516* or {@code null} for default / not applicable
517* @return the encoded message (the char values range from 0 to 928)
518*/
519std::vector<int>
520HighLevelEncoder::EncodeHighLevel(const std::wstring& msg, Compaction compaction, CharacterSet encoding)
521{
522 std::vector<int> highLevel;
523 highLevel.reserve(highLevel.size() + msg.length());
524
525 //the codewords 0..928 are encoded as Unicode characters
526 if (encoding != CharacterSet::ISO8859_1) {
527 EncodingECI(CharacterSetECI::ValueForCharset(encoding), highLevel);
528 }
529
530 int len = Size(msg);
531 int p = 0;
532 int textSubMode = SUBMODE_ALPHA;
533
534 // User selected encoding mode
535 if (compaction == Compaction::TEXT) {
536 EncodeText(msg, p, len, textSubMode, highLevel);
537
538 }
539 else if (compaction == Compaction::BYTE) {
540 std::string bytes = TextEncoder::FromUnicode(msg, encoding);
541 EncodeBinary(bytes, p, Size(bytes), BYTE_COMPACTION, highLevel);
542 }
543 else if (compaction == Compaction::NUMERIC) {
544 highLevel.push_back(LATCH_TO_NUMERIC);
545 EncodeNumeric(msg, p, len, highLevel);
546
547 }
548 else {
549 int encodingMode = TEXT_COMPACTION; //Default mode, see 4.4.2.1
550 while (p < len) {
551 int n = DetermineConsecutiveDigitCount(msg, p);
552 if (n >= 13) {
553 highLevel.push_back(LATCH_TO_NUMERIC);
554 encodingMode = NUMERIC_COMPACTION;
555 textSubMode = SUBMODE_ALPHA; //Reset after latch
556 EncodeNumeric(msg, p, n, highLevel);
557 p += n;
558 }
559 else {
560 int t = DetermineConsecutiveTextCount(msg, p);
561 if (t >= 5 || n == len) {
562 if (encodingMode != TEXT_COMPACTION) {
563 highLevel.push_back(LATCH_TO_TEXT);
564 encodingMode = TEXT_COMPACTION;
565 textSubMode = SUBMODE_ALPHA; //start with submode alpha after latch
566 }
567 textSubMode = EncodeText(msg, p, t, textSubMode, highLevel);
568 p += t;
569 }
570 else {
571 int b = DetermineConsecutiveBinaryCount(msg, p);
572 if (b == 0) {
573 b = 1;
574 }
575 std::string bytes = TextEncoder::FromUnicode(msg.substr(p, b), encoding);
576 if (bytes.length() == 1 && encodingMode == TEXT_COMPACTION) {
577 //Switch for one byte (instead of latch)
578 EncodeBinary(bytes, 0, 1, TEXT_COMPACTION, highLevel);
579 }
580 else {
581 //Mode latch performed by encodeBinary()
582 EncodeBinary(bytes, 0, Size(bytes), encodingMode, highLevel);
583 encodingMode = BYTE_COMPACTION;
584 textSubMode = SUBMODE_ALPHA; //Reset after latch
585 }
586 p += b;
587 }
588 }
589 }
590 }
591 return highLevel;
592}
